WEBVTT

00:00.605 --> 00:01.687
<i>Previously, on</i> Cedar Cove--

00:01.689 --> 00:03.355
Roy told me everything
that John did.

00:03.657 --> 00:05.373
He wants me
to move to New York.

00:05.375 --> 00:06.825
I'm the new D.A.

00:06.827 --> 00:08.460
I want you to let me do
what I do best, Dad,

00:08.462 --> 00:09.294
and that is run this
business.

00:09.296 --> 00:10.595
You mean <i> my</i> business.

00:10.597 --> 00:12.597
I'm your new
Chief Financial Officer.

00:12.599 --> 00:14.799
I want us
to move in together.

00:21.108 --> 00:22.173
Mom.

00:22.175 --> 00:24.943
Maryellen!

00:24.945 --> 00:26.194
What are you doing?

00:26.196 --> 00:28.346
You weren't supposed to
be here until tomorrow!

00:28.348 --> 00:30.782
Oh! I caught
an earlier flight.

00:30.784 --> 00:32.250
Well, where is John?

00:32.252 --> 00:33.852
He'll be here
in a couple of days.

00:33.854 --> 00:37.155
He had to fill in
for a sick sous chef, so.

00:38.292 --> 00:40.408
Oh! It's so good
to be home.

00:41.762 --> 00:43.144
What?

00:43.146 --> 00:44.362
Okay. Spill it.

00:44.364 --> 00:45.530
Spill what?

00:45.532 --> 00:46.498
What's wrong?

00:46.500 --> 00:48.900
Mom.

00:48.902 --> 00:50.652
I'm just here for a visit.

00:51.872 --> 00:54.973
I missed you
and I had the time off.

00:54.975 --> 00:56.041
Swear.

00:56.043 --> 00:57.309
Really?

00:57.311 --> 00:59.811
I just miss you, Mom.

01:00.948 --> 01:03.515
Oh. I miss you, too.

01:07.621 --> 01:10.188
Peggy and Moon
really outdid themselves.

01:10.190 --> 01:12.657
Mm, yeah,
I loved the lobster.

01:14.895 --> 01:17.028
So, how much
more small-talk

01:17.030 --> 01:18.030
do we have to do

01:18.031 --> 01:19.331
before we talk about

01:19.333 --> 01:21.900
what you clearly don't
want to talk about?

01:21.902 --> 01:24.369
You're right.

01:24.371 --> 01:25.503
Moving in together,

01:25.505 --> 01:28.340
it is the next step for us.

01:28.342 --> 01:30.909
I think we need to boldly go

01:30.911 --> 01:32.544
where neither one
of us have gone

01:32.546 --> 01:34.896
since we got divorced--

01:34.898 --> 01:37.248
living with someone
that we love,

01:37.250 --> 01:39.267
and I do love you.

01:39.269 --> 01:41.619
Love is not the issue.

01:41.621 --> 01:43.655
Dating is supposed to
lead to something,

01:43.657 --> 01:44.956
or away from something.

01:44.958 --> 01:47.208
It's a big decision.

01:47.210 --> 01:48.827
And I'm committed to you

01:48.829 --> 01:51.496
and to making
what we have work.

01:51.498 --> 01:52.964
Okay.

01:52.966 --> 01:55.400
All right. How about...

01:55.402 --> 01:56.868
you sleep on it

01:56.870 --> 01:58.837
and then we'll have
dinner tomorrow night

01:58.839 --> 02:01.406
and we'll talk
about it some more?

02:01.408 --> 02:03.742
I can commit to that.

02:03.744 --> 02:05.777
Okay.

02:13.887 --> 02:15.453
[door shuts]

02:19.926 --> 02:22.110
[phone rings]

02:22.996 --> 02:24.629
[sighs heavily]

02:24.631 --> 02:25.897
Hey, Jeri.

02:25.899 --> 02:27.999
I need you in Seattle
tomorrow for notes.

02:28.001 --> 02:29.701
Why don't you just
send me your notes?

02:29.703 --> 02:30.902
<i>Look, Jack.</i>

02:30.904 --> 02:32.670
<i>This is a new
relationship for us--</i>

02:32.672 --> 02:35.106
editor/writer, boss/employee.

02:36.243 --> 02:37.308
<i>I just want to make sure</i>

02:37.310 --> 02:39.344
nothing's lost in
translation.

02:39.346 --> 02:41.046
All right. [sighs]

02:41.048 --> 02:43.515
I'll be on the morning ferry,

02:43.517 --> 02:45.200
<i>but I need to be
back here for dinner.</i>

02:45.202 --> 02:46.384
Short leash.

02:46.386 --> 02:49.821
Not a leash. Love.

02:49.823 --> 02:52.090
A foreign concept to you,
I know, Jeri.

02:52.092 --> 02:54.392
Funny.

02:59.566 --> 03:02.267
[♪♪]

03:02.291 --> 03:05.791
www.addic7ed.com

03:07.000 --> 03:13.074
